This paper presents an axiomatic framework for decision making under uncertainty, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Sugeno integrals, which are a type of fuzzy logic, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of soft computing (cs.SI). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
